# Web Design Guidelines

Review web interfaces for accessibility, usability, and WCAG compliance.

## Priority Rules

| Category | Impact |
|----------|--------|
| Accessibility | CRITICAL |
| Semantic HTML | HIGH |
| Keyboard Navigation | HIGH |
| ARIA Patterns | MEDIUM-HIGH |
| Responsive Design | MEDIUM |

## Accessibility (CRITICAL)

### Color Contrast
- Normal text: 4.5:1 minimum
- Large text (≥18px bold): 3:1 minimum
- UI components: 3:1 minimum

### Focus States
```css
/* ❌ BAD */
button:focus { outline: none; }

/* ✅ GOOD */
button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #0066cc;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

### Alt Text
```html
<!-- ✅ Descriptive -->
<img src="hero.jpg" alt="Team collaborating" />

<!-- ✅ Decorative -->
<img src="decoration.svg" alt="" role="presentation" />
```

### Icon-Only Buttons
```html
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- icon --></svg>
</button>
```

## Semantic HTML

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<header><nav>...</nav></header>
<main>...</main>
<footer>...</footer>

<!-- ❌ BAD: Div soup -->
<div class="header"><div class="nav">...</div></div>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

- Tab order matches visual order
- Skip links present
- Modals trap focus
- Escape closes dialogs

## Quick Checklist

- [ ] Images have alt text
- [ ] Form inputs have labels
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Heading hierarchy sequential
- [ ] Color contrast meets 4.5:1
- [ ] Touch targets ≥44x44px
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` respected

